/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=treefallingquietly>treefallingquietly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 5:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   When do mages begin soloing HGs and/or gornit?</span><hr size=1> about to hit 35.  just curious when I should begin trying these? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 352<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 6:02:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When do mages begin soloing HGs and/or gornit?</span><hr size=1> You &quot;can&quot; solo HGs at 35, but you shouldn't. My suggestion is to wait til 44 when they're much more manageable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shlakor>Shlakor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 6:18:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When do mages begin soloing HGs and/or gornit?</span><hr size=1> Even 44 is a Pita. I suggest spend the time to get to 49. At 49, fire can take them, but at 49 its a hop skip and a jump to the 51 earth pet. at 51, you can park and farm some cash if ya like. Before then, its just not worth the time i think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1322<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 6:38:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When do mages begin soloing HGs and/or gornit?</span><hr size=1> Yes, HG's at 44 is good.  I did a lot of 44-49 there and made 1000's of plat. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 7:42:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   HG/Gornit</span><hr size=1> Whack some Golras and Tundra Yeti and you'll be 44 before you know it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kylere>Kylere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 326<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 7:52:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HG/Gornit</span><hr size=1> A 39 Mage can do Gornit, you will have to burn like a madman, but it can be done. Handy thing is of course you can blow all your mana and have 6 minutes to regen it back.<br>
<br>
I would highly recommend Earth Pet with a damage shield, and if you have Jboots you will not die like you will without them. As you have to burn to keep pet alive, he will break pet root and chase you, this is a solid downside as the guy can whack you from half a beach away.<br>
<br>
You could of course do earth pet chains, but chaining is laming I always say.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25992">Kylere Ap'Kailere -60th Archmage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> //  Kailere Drowsbane -55th Paladin<br>
