<br>
At 44, he's easy.  At 49, you'll be picking off seafurbies to fill up your time while waiting for him to respawn.  At 51, you'll mostly be hunting seafurbies, and killing Gornit when he pops.<br>
<br>
Doing HG's at 39 is pretty easy, though.  I farmed my way through 40th, as I remember. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=apollonike>apollonike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 11:55:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gornit</span><hr size=1> HG's are cake for a 49 beastlord, pet eats them up alone.  Would assume mages can do the same thing.<br>
<br>
<br>
kegulik <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 12:01:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HG/Gornit</span><hr size=1> With the summoned focii it should be even easier to kill them now at 39 than in days long gone. Gak, I was level 39 in November of '99 that was before even pet heals, and you could do them with chained Fire pets and bolts. <p><br>
