For the light of a candle to be seen, it must be taken to a dark place. -- UKLG</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanbun>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 538<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 12:03:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Chaincasting</span><hr size=1> I chaincasted him down easily at 34. Problem is, I had past Mage experience with that char, most 34s can't chaincast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#333333>(10/29/02 7:59:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7613.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chaincasting</span><hr size=1> I always laugh when I hear people talk about chaincasting before 44 or so.  It's just not that good of a strategy at those levels.  Chaincasting is all about the pet lasting long enough for the DS to do serious damage.  At low levels, the earth pet just doesn't have the hit points to allow the strategy to work.<br>
<br>
Take chaincasting Gornit at 34.  Your 34th level earth pet has about 1000hps.  Gornit has 2500hps and hits for a max of 96.  Your DS does 15 max.<br>
<br>
Assume Gornit does an average of 75pts per hit.  That means 13 hits will take out your pet.  13x15=195 damage from the DS.  Assume (generously) that your pet doubles that total with his fists... that's 400hps damage per pet to Gornit.  Let's also assume that the pet's root sticks every time, and you don't fizzle ever, so that you can chaincast in perfect safety.<br>
<br>
That means you'll need to cast 6 pets to kill Gornit at level 34.  6x200=1200.  6x120(DS)=720.  1050+720=1770 mana required to kill Gornit.  Let's also assume a 10% reduction in mana required due to focus items, specialization, etc.  So, you'll need a nice round 1600 mana to kill Gornit.<br>
<br>
A 34th level maxed out Erudite, starting with 142 int, and with 200 int after items, has about 1428 mana.<br>
<br>
The only way you could &quot;easily&quot; chaincast Gornit is if you got lucky and got the low level version of him, were twinked beyond belief, and had no fizzles or bobbles.<br>
<br>
