<br>
But, if you are broke like I was, you can do this at 39th.  It is a good tough fight.   I would avoid Gornit and do Rathe Mnts or South Ro, since you might want a zone nearby.<br>
<br>
Chaincasting pets is not a good tactic in itself for giants at 39th.    Yes, you should know how to do this, and be prepared to chain a pet if your original one goes down, but you should not simply rely on chaining to do the majority of the damage.   Your pets cannot take it and you don't have the mana to sustain it.  Giant will kill a level 39th pet in like 30-45 seconds if it is straight up tanking.<br>
<br>
You should emphasize nukes for killing giants.   In your 30's, with Blaze and Cinder Bolt, you nuke harder than a Wizzy, ya know?<br>
<br>
My method:   Overburn pulling for the 39th Mage<br>
<br>
How:  Prep an Earth pet with summoned armor, Burnout, and damage shield.   Med back mana to full.    Be SoWed or have Jboots.   Park pet in a nice safe spot, and go out and pick a giant to kill.<br>
<br>
Standing off at maximum bolt range, fire two cinder bolts at him.    If both hit for near or full damage, you should be well prepared to win the fight.   As the giant closes with you, run back towards your pet.   Try to get enough range to get a third nuke in (Blaze) before your pet actually engages.  At this point giant should be already 1/2 dead.  If it resists most of these nukes, just zone, don't waste any more time and mana because you are not going to win.<br>
<br>
Immediately run around in a large circle while your pet beats on the giant.   Eventually, your pet will get a root off or will taunt.  Stop running, and nuke 1 to 3 more times with blaze.   Run around and circle again if you regain aggro.  Giant dies, you loot.<br>
<br>
It takes some practice not getting hit by the giant in all this.   Expect to screw up a couple times until you get the hang of it.   The key is not to get hit at all and never get stunned by the giant -- which is actually rather easy once you get a great idea as to their large hit range.<br>
<br>
At the end of the fight you may be oom, but you should win unless you get a bunch of resists.  Don't be shy about zoning either -- you will have a heck of a time beating the highest level giants no matter what your tectic.  They have a large range of levels and the top giants are around level 39 to 40 == lots of hit points and better resists. <br>
At 44th, you can kill giants with a couple of nukes and pet tanking.<br>
<br>
At 49th, pets can solo a giant, with nukes you can take multiples at once.<br>
<br>
At 51+, pet can solo 2 or more giants, and you both can take many more at once using rains, nukes, pet heals. <p>Seek Pyremaker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
